Detailed Description

The class to provide base infomation for helping to access Data table, which is stored more detail data about Contacts.

Such as phone number, email address, group membership, nick anme, and so on.

The following example demonstrates how to use this Data class.

 getColumn(){
     String id            = Data::_ID();
     String mimetype      = Data::MIMETYPE();
     String emailAddress  = Data::Email::ADDRESS();
 }

 getMimeType(){
     String eamilMimeType = Data::Email::CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE();
     String eventMimeType = Data::Email::CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE();
 }

 getType(){
     int32_t              = Data::Email::Type::CUSTOM;
     int32_t              = Data::Email::Type::OTHER;
 }

 getTypeName(){
     Context context(this); // this is mean page instance
     String emailTypeName =
        Data::Email::getTypeName(*context.getResources(),Data::Email::Type::CUSTOM);
     String eventTypeName =
        Data::Event::getTypeName(*context.getResources(),Data::Event::Type::OTHER);
 }

static const gaia::base::String gaia::content::Data::IS_SUPER_PRIMARY ( ) [static]

Whether this is the primary entry of its kind for the aggregate contact it belongs to.

Any data record that is "super primary" must also be "primary". For example, the super-primary entry may be interpreted as the default contact value of its kind (for example, the default phone number to use for the contact).
